$lang['Hexadecimal is a way of representing binary data in human-readable form. It was developed in the 19th century to allow computers to store large amounts of information.'] = 'Hexadecimal ye kunnafonidilan fila jiracogo ye hadamaden ka kalancogo la. A dabɔra san kɛmɛ 19nan na walisa ɔridinatɛriw ka se ka kunnafoni caman mara.';
$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Aw bɛ se ka baara kɛ ni hexadecimal ye walasa ka fɛn caman sɛmɛntiya tannan ni binary nafaw cɛ. Misali la, n’i ye 10011011001010 sɛmɛntiya ka kɛ hexadecimal ye, o bɛna kɛ 0x4F ye. O kɔrɔ ye ko nafa 4F bɛ jateden fila jira 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Jatebla ni ɔridinatɛri dɔnniya la, hexadecimal (basi 16 fana, walima hex) ye jɔyɔrɔ jatebɔcogo ye min ka radix, walima base, ye 16. A bɛ baara kɛ ni taamasiyɛn danfaralen tan ni wɔɔrɔ ye, a ka c’a la, taamasiyɛn 0–9 ye walasa ka nafaw jira zeru fo kɔnɔntɔn, ani A, B, C, D, E, F (walima a–f cogo wɛrɛ la) walasa ka nafa tan fo tan ni duuru jira. Misali la, jateden wɔɔrɔnan 2AF3 bɛ bɛn, tannan na, ni (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , walima 10.995 ye.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Jateden wɔɔrɔ kelen-kelen bɛɛ bɛ jateden fila (bits) naani jira (a bɛ fɔ fana ko &quot;nibble&quot;), wa jateden wɔɔrɔnan baara fɔlɔ ye i n’a fɔ jateden fila kofɔlenw jiracogo min bɛ hadamadenw fɛ ɔridinatɛri ni ɛntɛrinɛti nizɛrikan na. Misali la, bayt hakɛw bɛ se ka bɔ 0 la ka se 255 ma (tanan) nka u bɛ se ka jira ka ɲɛ i n’a fɔ jateden wɔɔrɔ fila minnu bɛ 00 fo FF cɛ. Hexadecimal fana bɛ kɛ ka caya walasa ka ɔridinatɛri hakilijagabɔ ladɛrɛsiw jira.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex ye Hexadecimal surunyalen ye, min sinsinnen bɛ basigi -16 sigicogo kan, wa a bɛ kɛ ka ɔridinatɛriw ka cikanw jiracogo nɔgɔya. Nin taamasiyɛn 16 jatebla in Dabɔra i n’a fɔ fɛɛrɛ min bɛ jatebla 8-bit fila-fila bali, o la kunnafoniw bɛ Se ka kodɔn ɔridinatɛriw kɔnɔ k’a sɔrɔ cɛsiri ma Kɛ. A bɛ se ka sɛbɛn ani ka sɛbɛnni kɛ ni hex nimɔrɔ fila ye minnu tɛ kelen ye ni hex digiti kelen-kelen bɛɛ bɛ nibble walima laala 4-bits cogoya jira.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Nin jatebla in bɛ baara Kɛ ni taamaʃyɛn 16 ye minnu bɛ Jira 0-9 walima AF cɛ. 0–9 bɛ jatedenw jira fo ka se kɔnɔntɔn ma k’a sɔrɔ AF bɛ jateden 10–15 jira. Ni i y’a suma ni jatebla suguya saba tɔw ye, jatebla wɔɔrɔnan bɛ jate jatebla ye min bɛ baara Kɛ kosɛbɛ.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Aw ka kode hexadecimal (kode hexadecimal) tɛ tiɲɛ ye';
